******
[2]
Date: 12 Jun 2012
Source: Cross Online Bulgarian Network [edited]
http://www.cross.bg/1307173


Nobody had consumed meat from infected cows in the village of kaolinovskoto Takach. That said, a 40 year old man was placed yesterday in Shumen hospital with suspected anthrax. He had rash lesions on his hands after contact with meat from the slaughtered animal. His condition is good, and is under antibiotic treatment.

The animal was slaughtered on Friday [8 Jun 2012], attended by 11 villagers. The carcass of the infected animal is being rendered. Samples of meat were sent to the national diagnostic laboratory in Sofia. "The results will be known within a few days," said Dr Katya Dimitrova, director of the Food Safety Agency in Shumen.

